member.summary:
                 Automatically renders any ASPX page into PDF instead of Html.  Use it in the Page_Load
                 Event.

Example:protected void Page_Load(object sender, EventArgs e){ 
                   IronPdf.AspxToPdf.RenderThisPageAsPdf(FileBehavior.Attachment, "MyPdf.pdf", new  PdfPrintOptions(){ Dpi = 300 });
                 }

A Html Header or Footer which will be printed onto every page of the PDF. This can be used to override and
When using HtmlHeaderFooter it is important to set and
Merge meta-data into your html using any of these placeholder strings: {page} {total-pages} {url} {date} {time} {html-title} {pdf-title}
